{
  "texts": [
    "Such phenomena are crude descriptions of the actual dynamics unfolding in the Earth system 60, which is why moving to dense meteorological FMs is both promising and necessary 21.",
    "On land, distinguishing between hazard and impact forecasts blurs.",
    "Consider the European Floods use case: traditional hydrological models for stream flow forecasts needed basin-specific tuning.",
    "However, treating stream flow forecasts as a time series, Long Short-Term Neural Networks (LSTMs) trained on cross-basin data outperform previous methods 61, 62.",
    "Google FloodHub operationalizes this, providing flood forecasts in over 80 countries, offering early warnings to large populations 63."
  ]
}